From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 16:40:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kati: lib-only de-workspace + embedded-engine patches + sarun
 testcases
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Re-applies sarun's delta over the pristine kati base:
  * Cargo.toml: de-workspace to a standalone crate — drop the criterion
    [[bench]], the linux tikv-jemallocator global allocator, the gperf
    feature, and the find_emulator bin; gate the rkati [[bin]] behind a
    kati-corpus feature; add regex-lite/tempfile dev-deps for the corpus test.
  * Cargo.lock: regenerated for the de-worked manifest.
  * src-rs/*.rs (15 files): the sarun '// sarun:' embedded-engine patches
    (in-process execution, logical I/O, GNU make 4.3 compat fixes); drop the
    jemalloc allocator from main.rs.
  * testcase/: revert 5 upstream cases touched by sarun and add the 82
    sarun_* compat cases.
  * tests/corpus.rs: the make-vs-rkati compat harness (kati-corpus feature).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
